  <p>A1. Lesson 4.5.</p>
  <break time="700ms"/>
  <p><prosody rate="86%">Listen and repeat.</prosody></p>
  <p><prosody rate="86%">family.</prosody></p><break time="700ms"/><p><prosody rate="86%">family.</prosody></p><break time="700ms"/><p><prosody rate="86%">there is/there are.</prosody></p><break time="700ms"/><p><prosody rate="86%">there is/there are.</prosody></p><break time="700ms"/><p><prosody rate="86%">speaking.</prosody></p><break time="700ms"/><p><prosody rate="86%">speaking.</prosody></p><break time="700ms"/><p><prosody rate="86%">Places,.</prosody></p><break time="700ms"/><p><prosody rate="86%">Places,.</prosody></p><break time="700ms"/>
  <p><prosody rate="86%">Now say the full sentence.</prosody></p>
  <p><prosody rate="86%">Example 1: I can use there is/there are to talk about family.</prosody></p>
